"Dembski S., Masson G., Monnier D., Wagner P., Pihan J.C.","Consequences of elevated temperatures on life-history traits of an introduced fish, pumpkinseed Lepomis gibbosus",2006,"Journal of Fish Biology","69","2",,"331","346",,,10.1111/j.1095-8649.2006.01087.x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33746468647&partnerID=40&md5=5028392a1ec34571105f05184d825e0c","Laboratoire Biodiversité et Fonctionnement des Ecosystèmes, UFR Sci. F.A., Université de Metz, R. du Gén. Delestraint, 57070 Metz, France; Conseil Supérieur de la Pêche, Délégation Régionale Champagne Ardennes, Lorraine, Alsace, 23 rue des Garennes, 57155 Marly, France","Dembski, S., Laboratoire Biodiversité et Fonctionnement des Ecosystèmes, UFR Sci. F.A., Université de Metz, R. du Gén. Delestraint, 57070 Metz, France; Masson, G., Laboratoire Biodiversité et Fonctionnement des Ecosystèmes, UFR Sci. F.A., Université de Metz, R. du Gén. Delestraint, 57070 Metz, France; Monnier, D., Conseil Supérieur de la Pêche, Délégation Régionale Champagne Ardennes, Lorraine, Alsace, 23 rue des Garennes, 57155 Marly, France; Wagner, P., Laboratoire Biodiversité et Fonctionnement des Ecosystèmes, UFR Sci. F.A., Université de Metz, R. du Gén. Delestraint, 57070 Metz, France; Pihan, J.C., Laboratoire Biodiversité et Fonctionnement des Ecosystèmes, UFR Sci. F.A., Université de Metz, R. du Gén. Delestraint, 57070 Metz, France","Life-history reactions of a pumpkinseed Lepomis gibbosus population in north-eastern France exposed to heated waters were studied. The study was conducted from 2001 to 2003 in an artificial reservoir, adjacent to a nuclear power plant, in which water temperatures are cool in winter (8.2-12.4°C) and rise early in spring (April: 14.7°C) nearly 5°C and 3°C over the temperature of its tributary, respectively. Fast growth among young-of-the-year, precocious maturity and short life span were observed, in contrast to related studies. The short life span appeared to be the price paid for early maturity in breeding fish, which suffered high mortality rates just after their first reproduction. © 2006 The Fisheries Society of the British Isles.","Global warming; Lepomis gibbosus; Longevity; Reproductive strategy; Sexual maturation","fish; introduced species; invasive species; life history trait; mortality; nuclear power plant; population density; reproductive strategy; reservoir; sexual maturity; temperature effect; Eurasia; Europe; France; Western Europe; Lepomis gibbosus",,,,,,"Alm, G., Connection between maturity, size and age in fishes (1959) Reports from the Institute of Freshwater Research, Drottningholm, 40, pp. 5-145; Arendt, J.D., Wilson, D.S., Optimistic growth: Competition and an ontogenetic niche-shift select for rapid growth in pumpkinseed sunfish (Lepomis gibbosus) (1997) Evolution, 51, pp. 1946-1954; Arendt, J.D., Wilson, D.S., Countergradient selection for rapid growth in pumpkinseed sunfish: Disentangling ecological and evolutionary effects (1999) Ecology, 80, pp. 2793-2798; Atkinson, D., Temperature and organism size - A biological law for ectotherms? (1994) Advances in Ecological Research, 25, pp. 1-58; Atkinson, D., Effects of temperature on the size of aquatic ectotherms: Exceptions to the general rule (1995) Journal of Thermal Biology, 20, pp. 61-74; Atkinson, D., Sibly, R.M., Why are organisms usually bigger in colder environments? Making sense of a life history puzzle (1997) Trends in Ecology and Evolution, 12, pp. 235-239; Bagliniere, J.L., Le Louarn, H., Scale characteristics of the main freshwater fish species in France (1987) Bulletin Français de la Pêche et de la Pisciculture, 306, pp. 2-39; Belk, M.C., Predator-induced delayed maturity in bluegill sunfish (Lepomis macrochirus): Variation among populations (1998) Oecologia, 113, pp. 203-209; Bell, G., The costs of reproduction and their consequences (1980) American Naturalist, 116, pp. 45-76; Berrigan, D., Charnov, E.L., Reaction norms for age and size at maturity in response to tempe